**Definition:** Let $\sigma \in S_n$. Define $\sgn(\sigma) = (-1)^{N(\sigma)}$, where $N(\sigma)$ is the number of inversions in $\sigma$. Here, an ___inversion___ is a pair $(\sigma(i), \sigma(j))$ such that $i < j$ and $\sigma(i) > \sigma(j)$.

